== Welcome to Railfrog Reference Application

=== Prerequirements

You need to have following:

1. Ruby interpreter. See http://www.ruby-lang.org
2. Rails. Run gem install rails -y
3. SQLite or MySQL. Find full list of supported databases at http://api.rubyonrails.com/files/vendor/rails/activerecord/README.html
4. Install mime-types gem:

  gem install mime-types 


=== Installation

# Grab our empty Rails 2.0.2 application with installed Railfrog:

  svn co https://svn.versiondude.net/railfrog/cms/reference_application/trunk railfrog

# Edit config/database.yml if you need

# Run

  rake db:migrate


=== How to use Railfrog

Start service by running script/server and open http://localhost:3000/admin

